  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Aarti, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, the monsoon makes me sleepy too, but I find warm chai helps shake it off. How was your day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Miss Maya! My day was okay. I studied a bit for NEET PG, but I got tired too. I had chai, like you said, but I still feel slow. How do you stay so fresh in this weather? ☔"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Got it. The monsoon can really weigh you down. I get that, it's like the whole world slows down. What helps you power through?\""
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I try to take short breaks and listen to classical music it helps me focus again. But some days, I just can't. Exam stress is real. Today I revised respiratory system and it felt good. Aapki tarah chai peene ki koshish bhi kar rahi hoon. 🍵"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Short breaks with music, smart! The respiratory system is a good chunk to crack. I get how exam stress piles up."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Yeah, sometimes I feel like my brain is full of fog. I cook kadhai to take my mind off studies, but I end up thinking about exams even while cooking. Maybe I should try studying with some light music on...?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Foggy brain days, I get that. Mixing study and cooking is a tight balance. What kind of music do you think might help?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I like ghazals or instrumental music when I study. It’s calm. But sometimes I play Marathi folk songs while cooking—it makes me feel better. Maybe I can try ghazals while cooking too? 🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Ghazals are calming, they could work for cooking too. What’s one dish you’d cook with music on?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Pav bhaji! It's my go-to comfort food. I turn on some old Marathi film songs and just let the music and the sizzling onions fill the kitchen. But I also want to try making it while listening to ghazals, like you said. Maybe it will help me relax more? What do you cook when you need to unwind?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Pav bhaji and music make a perfect combo, sizzling onions and old songs are a win. What’s one recipe you’d love to try next?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I’ve been wanting to try making authentic Italian pasta—it sounds fancy and maybe will give me a break from Indian flavors for a bit. But I’m a bit nervous I’ll mess it up. Have you ever tried cooking something totally new and failed? 😅"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Italian pasta sounds like a fun challenge, fancy but doable! Everyone messes up once in a while. What’s the first step you’d take with the pasta?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I’d start by watching a few videos so I don’t confuse the steps. Maybe get the right ingredients first—like fresh pasta, tomato sauce, basil. I’m scared I might overcook it, but maybe if I play some ghazal in the background, I’ll calm down. What about you? Do you cook with music too? 🍝🎶"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Videos and fresh ingredients are smart starts, ghazal will definitely help you stay calm. What’s your favorite kind of pasta?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "My favorite is spaghetti aglio e olio—it sounds so fancy, but I think it’s simple. I have to find the right olive oil first. Maybe I’ll invite my friend to try it when I make it. I hope I don’t mess it up… but if I do, at least I’ll have music to blame! 😊"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Spaghetti aglio e olio is a great pick, olive oil makes all the difference. Will you play ghazals or Marathi songs while making it?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I think I’ll go with ghazals this time—maybe a Lata Mangeshkar song to keep me calm. But if the pasta cries for a Marathi tune, I’ll switch! 😊 I should probably get cooking now, or I’ll never try it. Talk to you later, Miss Maya!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Got it. Lata Mangeshkar with your pasta, sounds perfect. Go for it, and tell me how it turns out later. Talk soon!"
    }
  ],
